    <title>mock-torznab</title>
    <!--
      Sizes deliberately small (~80 MB / 250 MB instead of realistic
      8 GB / 25 GB). `grab_release` enforces a free-disk-space check
      (`ensure_free_space_for_grab`: release_size + 2 GB buffer) and
      bails if the test's tempdir filesystem reports less free space
      than the buffer. CI runners' /tmp can dip under 10 GB during
      heavy parallel test load — when that happens the grab silently
      fails and downstream "no download row" assertions look like
      logic bugs. None of the consuming tests assert on size values.
    -->
